BT 0 g /F2 12 Tf 36 608 Td (Chapter 15: Resources and Getting Help) Tj ET
q 0.4 G 1 w 36 600 m 396 600 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 575 Td (National resources: AARP Connect2Affect, Eldercare Locator \(800-677-1116\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 554 Td (Crisis support: 988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline, Crisis Text Line \(text HOME to 741741\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 533 Td (Free technology training: OATS \(Older Adults Technology Services\), local libraries.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 512 Td (Senior center programs: Most communities offer free social activities and classes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 491 Td (Volunteer matching: VolunteerMatch.org and AARP volunteer programs connect you with purpose.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 470 Td (AI companion tools: ElliQ, Replika \(free\), Pi \(free\), Amazon Echo with Alexa.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 449 Td (Social platforms: Stitch, Meetup, Facebook Groups, Nextdoor, SilverSneakers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 428 Td (Telehealth therapy: BetterHelp, Talkspace, and Medicare-covered online counseling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 407 Td (Share this book with someone who might be struggling with isolation silently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 386 Td (Ask your doctor about loneliness - they can connect you with local resources.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 365 Td (Remember: asking for connection is brave, not weak. Everyone needs community.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9.8 Tf 36 344 Td (You deserve to feel connected, valued, and part of something meaningful every day.) Tj ET

endstream
